Tags:
  - Discernment-Truth=Knowledge=The Knowledge of One's Ignorance
  - Discernment-Truth=Knowledge=Belief and Practice
By: Abû Sa'id ibn Abi ’l-Khayr
---
First, action is necessary, then knowledge, in order that thou mayest know that
thou knowest naught and art no one. This is not easy to know. It is a thing
that cannot be rightly learned by instruction, nor sewed on with needle nor
tied on with thread. It is the gift of God.
